# BasePopover

GSAP-powered popover with a mask-reveal animation — content slides in from the placement direction through a soft gradient edge, with physics-based easing (overshoot + bounce). No opacity transition, pure spatial reveal.

Panels use `TxCard`; control appearance via `panelBackground / panelShadow / panelRadius / panelPadding`.

## Basic Usage

### BasePopover
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BasePopoverBasicDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const open = ref(false)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxBasePopover v-model="open" placement="bottom-start">
      <template #reference>
        <TxButton @click="open = !open">Click</TxButton>
      </template>

      <div style="width: 220px; padding: 4px;">
        Popover content with mask-reveal animation.
      </div>
    </TxBasePopover>
  </template>
---
:::

## Soft Edge

Control the gradient softness at the mask boundary via `soft-edge` (px). A larger value creates a wider gradient fade.

### Soft Edge
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BasePopoverSplitLineDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const open = ref(false)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxBasePopover
      v-model="open"
      placement="bottom-start"
      :soft-edge="24"
    >
      <template #reference>
        <TxButton @click="open = !open">Soft Edge</TxButton>
      </template>

      <div style="width: 240px; padding: 4px;">
        Content emerges with a soft gradient edge.
      </div>
    </TxBasePopover>
  </template>
---
:::

## Placement

Content enters and exits from the placement direction. For `top`, content slides down from above and returns upward on close.

